    • Field Detail

      • FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE

        public static final java.lang.String FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains full document. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying of full document image is enabled (see setDisplayFullDocumentImage(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)

      • setDisplayFullDocumentImage

        public void setDisplayFullDocumentImage(boolean displayFullDocumentImage)
        Sets whether full document image should be sent to MetadataListener. If enabled, image will be of type ImageType.DEWARPED, and name of the image (see Image.getImageName()) will be equal to FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE, so make sure you subscribe to receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED images with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)
        Parameters:
        displayFullDocumentImage - whether full document image should be sent to MetadataListener.

      • setDetectGlare

        public void setDetectGlare(boolean detectGlare)
        Description copied from interface: GlareDetectorOptions
        Defines whether glare detector will be used during recognition process. By default this option is set to true and glare detector is used. If the glare detector is used and obtaining of glare metadata is enabled in MetadataSettings with method MetadataSettings.setGlareMetadataAllowed(boolean), glare status will be reported to MetadataListener. Also when glare is detected OCR will not be performed on the affected document position to prevent errors in the extracted data.
        Specified by:
        setDetectGlare in interface GlareDetectorOptions
        Parameters:
        detectGlare - whether glare detector will be used during recognition process.
